              margin-top: 2px !important;">U.S. v. Skrmetti</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The Supreme Court had its first hearing of the <a href="https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/landmark-supreme-court-case-weighs-gender-affirming-care/story?id=116232587" target="_blank">U.S. v. Skrmetti</a> case. The case challenges Tennessee’s ban on gender-affirming medical care for minors, with significant implications for transgender rights. The plaintiffs include families of transgender teens. They argue the law discriminates based on sex, which violates the <a href="https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/equal_protection" target="_blank">Equal Protection</a> Clause. Tennessee defends the ban as safeguarding minors from unproven medical interventions. Major U.S. medical groups <a href="https://www.aap.org/en/news-room/news-releases/aap/2021/american-academy-of-pediatrics-speaks-out-against-bills-harming-transgender-youth/" target="_blank">speak</a> out against the bill, while critics cite potential risks and insufficient long-term data. A ruling is expected by June 2025, although many expect the court will uphold the ban.</p>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
