              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Nun arrested</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Sister Anna Donelli, a Catholic nun affiliated with the Sisters of Charity Institute in Milan, was arrested as part of a significant <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/05/europe/catholic-nun-25-arrested-italy-intl-latam/index.html" target="_blank">mafia bust</a> in northern Italy. She is accused of acting as an intermediary for the ’Ndrangheta crime syndicate, passing messages and aiding criminal operations between prison inmates and outside associates. The police operation also led to the confiscation of $1.9 million in cash and special dogs identified drugs. Among the other arrests was a physician tied to the Brothers of Italy party, who allegedly treated mobsters’ injuries. Donelli is presently under house arrest.</p>
        </mj-text>
