              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">What are the issues surrounding Hunter Biden’s pardon?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The recent <a href="https://apnews.com/article/biden-hunter-biden-pardon-son-9307d6bade834df77c265cae7d3b7c25" target="_blank">pardon</a> of Hunter Biden has received mixed reactions from both sides of the political aisle, even among some <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/02/politics/biden-allies-disappointed-pardon/index.html" target="_blank">Democrat loyalists</a>. Critics <a href="https://x.com/TheSourceCNN/status/1863780202452590776" target="_blank">argue</a> that putting personal interests ahead of duty erodes the system's integrity and raises questions about fairness and timing. Some worry it sets a precedent where individuals connected to a president can feel above the law.</p>
        <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Speculation surrounds Kamala Harris’s potential impact on Biden’s decision. White House press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/02/politics/video/hunter-biden-pardon-jean-pierre-air-force-one-sot-digvid" target="_blank">suggested</a> that Biden might not have pardoned Hunter had Harris won the election. Historically, presidential pardons for <a href="https://www.newsweek.com/full-list-presidents-who-have-pardoned-relatives-joe-hunter-biden-1993960" target="_blank">family members</a> aren't new—Bill Clinton pardoned his half-brother, and Donald Trump pardoned Charles Kushner, Ivanka's father-in-law. Charles Kushner was additionally picked as the <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/americas/20241130-trump-picks-real-estate-mogul-charles-kushner-father-of-his-son-in-law-as-france-envoy" target="_blank">ambassador</a> to France.</p>
       <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">In summary, Biden's pardon mirrors Republican's <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-65007991" target="_blank">claims</a> of politically motivated prosecution, raising broader concerns about politicized justice and public distrust in institutions. Hunter Biden was proven guilty of gun possession and tax evasion charges. Both cases stemmed in 2019 when he struggled with alcohol and drug abuse.</p>
      
        </mj-text>
    </mj-column>
